Web Scrapping in R

Extract 11 features of top 100 movies from the imdb website

library(rvest)
url <- 'http://www.imdb.com/search/title?count=100&release_date=2018,2018&title_type=feature'
webpage <- read_html(url)
print("IMDB analysis of movies")
[1] "IMDB analysis of movies"

Rank

rank_data_html <- html_nodes(webpage,'.text-primary')
rank_data <- html_text(rank_data_html)
rank_data <- as.numeric(rank_data)

Title

Titles of first few movies

Description

cat("Reading the decsription of movies","\n")
description_data_html <- html_nodes(webpage,'.ratings-bar+ .text-muted')
description_data <- html_text(description_data_html)
head(description_data)

Runtime

cat("Reading the runtime of movies","\n")
Reading the runtime of movies 
runtime_data_html <- html_nodes(webpage,'.text-muted .runtime')
runtime_data <- html_text(runtime_data_html)
runtime_data <- gsub(" min","",runtime_data)
head(runtime_data)
[1] "134" "143" "130" "119" "136" "135"

Genre

cat("Reading the genre of the movies","\n")
Reading the genre of the movies 
genre_data_html <- html_nodes(webpage,'.genre')
genre_data <- html_text(genre_data_html)
genre_data <- gsub("\n","",genre_data)
genre_data <- gsub(" ","",genre_data)
genre_data <- gsub(",.*","",genre_data)
genre_data <- as.factor(genre_data)
head(genre_data)
[1] Biography Action    Biography Biography Drama     Drama    
Levels: Action Adventure Animation Biography Comedy Crime Drama Fantasy Horror Sci-Fi

Director & Actors

cat("Reading the directors and actors of the movies","\n")
Reading the directors and actors of the movies 
directors_data_html <- html_nodes(webpage,'.text-muted+ p a:nth-child(1)')
directors_data <- html_text(directors_data_html)
head(directors_data)
[1] "Bryan Singer"     "James Wan"        "Peter Farrelly"   "Yorgos Lanthimos" "Bradley Cooper"   "Alfonso Cuarón"  
directors_data <- as.factor(directors_data)
actors_data_html <- html_nodes(webpage,'.lister-item-content .ghost+ a')
actors_data <- html_text(actors_data_html)
head(actors_data)
[1] "Rami Malek"       "Jason Momoa"      "Viggo Mortensen"  "Olivia Colman"    "Lady Gaga"        "Yalitza Aparicio"
actors_data <- as.factor(actors_data)

Metascore

cat("Reading the meta score of movies","\n")
Reading the meta score of movies 
metascore_data_html <- html_nodes(webpage,'.metascore')
metascore_data <- html_text(metascore_data_html)
metascore_data <- gsub(" ","",metascore_data)
length(metascore_data)
[1] 97
for(i in c(52,65,67,88)){
  a <- metascore_data[1:(i-1)]
  b <- metascore_data[i:length(metascore_data)]
  metascore_data <- append(a,list("NA"))
  metascore_data <- append(metascore_data,b)
}
metascore_data <- metascore_data[1:100]
metascore_data <- as.numeric(metascore_data)
length(metascore_data)
[1] 100
summary(metascore_data)

Combining the 11 features into a data frame

movies_df <- data.frame(Rank = rank_data,Title = title_data,
                        Description = description_data,Runtime = runtime_data,
                        Genre = genre_data ,Rating = rating_data,
                        Metascore = metascore_data,Votes = votes_data,
                        Gross_Earning = gross_data,Director = directors_data,
                        Actor = actors_data)
